<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="363" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,745]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,685,710]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name of this species is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1012,1109,686,709]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">arcuatus</emphasis>
(arcuate), in reference to the arched lamella antevaginalis.
</paragraph>
